        "body": "<p>First, you can't ask in SO to find libraries.<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Questions asking us to recommend or find a book, tool, software library, tutorial or other off-site resource are off-topic for Stack Overflow as they tend to attract opinionated answers and spam. Instead, describe the problem and what has been done so far to solve it.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p><strong>To answer your question:<\/strong><br>\nYou don't need any API, third party software or a library to achieve this.<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Create a table for job executions in your database.<\/li>\n<li>Insert a record in each job execution in database.<\/li>\n<li>Make a select when needed.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n",
